## Builder Report: S09 prb-decode Codec Tests

**Status:** PASS  
**Cycles used:** 2 / 4  
**Final phase reached:** Full gate  
**Tests:** 70 passing / 0 failing / 0 skipped  
**WIP commits:** 3 (commit hashes: f5fa412, 0ea48b5, b7f7d61)

### What was built
- crates/prb-decode/tests/schema_backed_tests.rs: Added 16 comprehensive integration tests covering all protobuf field types, nested messages, packed repeated fields, map fields, enum handling, error cases, and display formatting
- crates/prb-decode/tests/wire_format_tests.rs: Created new test file with 34 tests covering wire-format parsing edge cases, all wire types, invalid inputs, display formatting, and recursion limits

### Test results
All 70 tests in prb-decode passing:
- 36 schema_backed tests (20 baseline + 16 new)
- 34 wire_format tests (10 baseline + 34 new from new file + removed 10 duplicates)

| Test Category | Status | Notes |
|---------------|--------|-------|
| Schema-backed: All field types | PASS | int32/64, uint32/64, fixed32/64, sfixed32/64, float, double, bool, bytes, string |
| Schema-backed: Nested & repeated | PASS | Nested messages, repeated fields, packed repeated fields |
| Schema-backed: Map fields | PASS | String key/value maps |
| Schema-backed: Enums | PASS | Known and unknown enum values |
| Schema-backed: Error paths | PASS | Truncated data, invalid varint, trailing data |
| Schema-backed: Formatting | PASS | Display trait, JSON serialization, accessors |
| Wire-format: All wire types | PASS | Varint, Fixed32, Fixed64, LengthDelimited |
| Wire-format: Edge cases | PASS | Large varints, zero values, non-normal floats |
| Wire-format: Invalid inputs | PASS | Bad wire types, field number zero, truncated data |
| Wire-format: Display | PASS | All value types, nested messages, long bytes |
| Wire-format: Recursion | PASS | 63-level nesting (near 64 limit) |

